    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix uninitialized variable bug in bfly3_256 FFT function\n\n### Summary\nThe NR PHY layer uses SIMD-optimized FFT implementations for signal processing. A critical bug was found in the `bfly3_256` function that caused incorrect FFT outputs during PUSCH demodulation. The issue occurred because temporary variables `tmpre` and `tmpim` were not initialized to zero before accumulation operations.\n\nThis bug caused PUSCH decoding failures, particularly noticeable with 256-QAM modulation where the SNR performance dropped significantly. Users observed up to 30% reduction in throughput during high-load scenarios.\n\nThe root cause was that `cmac_256` and `cmult_256` functions accumulate results into the temporary variables, but these variables contained garbage values from the stack. The bug was not present in all FFT sizes - only those using the radix-3 butterfly implementations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Added zero-initialization for `tmpre` and `tmpim` variables in `bfly3_256` function before complex multiplication operations.\n\n"
}